{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Creation

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the beginning when God created the heavens and the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}the earth was still unformed and chaotic,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with darkness on the surface of the abyss,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the spirit of God hovering over the waters.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}God said, \uc1\u8220*Let there be light,\uc1\u8221* and there was light.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}God saw that the light was good.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He separated the light from the darkness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}calling the light \uc1\u8217*day\uc1\u8217* and the darkness \uc1\u8217*night\uc1\u8217*.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There was an evening and a morning, making the first day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let there be a dome between the waters,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and let it separate the waters from the waters.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So God made the dome to separate the waters below
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
from the waters which were above it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}God called the dome the \uc1\u8217*sky\uc1\u8217*.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There was an evening and a morning, making the second day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let the waters under the sky be gathered together,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and let the dry ground appear.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}God called the dry ground \uc1\u8217*land\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and he called the gathered waters \uc1\u8217*seas\uc1\u8217*.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
God saw that it was good.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}God said, \uc1\u8220*Let the earth put forth vegetation:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Plants on the earth which yield their own kind of seed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and trees that bear fruits in which are their own seed.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The earth sprouted vegetation:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
seed-bearing plants,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and trees with seed-bearing fruit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
God saw that it was good.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}There was an evening and a morning, making the third day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let there be lights in the dome of the sky
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to separate the night from the day.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Let them be signs to mark the seasons, the days, and the years.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Let them be lights in the dome of the sky to light the earth.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}So God made the two great lights:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
The greater to rule the day and the lesser to rule the night.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
God made the stars also.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He placed all these lights in the dome of the sky
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
to shed light upon the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}to rule over the day and over the night,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and to separate light from darkness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
God saw that it was good.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}There was an evening and a morning, making the fourth day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let the waters teem with living creatures,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and let birds fly over the earth in the open dome of the sky.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}God created the great sea monsters,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
all kinds of living, moving creatures with which the waters teem,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and all kinds of winged birds.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
God saw that it was good.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}He blessed them, saying, \uc1\u8220*Be fruitful,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
increase, fill the oceans,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and let the birds increase on the land.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}There was an evening and a morning, making the fifth day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let the earth produce all kinds of living creatures:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
cattle and reptiles and wild beasts.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}So God made all the different kinds of wild beasts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the cattle, and everything that crawls upon the ground.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
God saw that it was good.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Then God said, \uc1\u8220*Let us make humans who are images of us, who are like us.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Let them rule over the fish of the sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the birds of the sky, the cattle, the wild beasts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and all the reptiles that crawl upon the ground.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}So God created humans in his image,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
he created them in the image of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
He created them male and female.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Then God blessed them, and said to them:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Be fruitful, grow in number,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
fill the earth and govern it;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
rule over the fish of the sea, the birds of the sky,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and over every living thing that crawls on the ground,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}God said, \uc1\u8220*I give you every seed-bearing plant
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
throughout all the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and every tree that has seed-bearing fruit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
They will be food for you,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}and to every wild beast and to every bird of the sky,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and to everything that crawls on the earth -
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
everything with the breath of life in it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
I give every green plant for food.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-1720\li2800
It was so.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}When God saw all that he had made,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he perceived that it was very good.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There was an evening and a morning, making the sixth day.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}So the heavens and the earth were finished, and everything in them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}When on the seventh day God finished the work which he had done,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
he rested that day from all his work.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}God blessed the seventh day and set it apart,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
for in it he rested from all the creative work which he had done.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The garden

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}This is the story of the heavens and earth when they were created.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
At the time when the {\scaps Lord} God made earth and heaven,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}there were not yet any plants on the earth, and no vegetation had sprung up; for the {\scaps Lord} God had not sent rain upon the earth, and there was no one to till the soil.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}A mist used to rise from the earth and water all the surface of the ground.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then the {\scaps Lord} God molded a human being out of dust taken from the ground and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life, and he became a living being.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The {\scaps Lord} God planted a garden in Eden, far in the East; and placed the human he had formed there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}From the soil the {\scaps Lord} God made grow all kinds of trees that are pleasant to look at and good for food, with the tree of life also in the middle of the garden and the tree that gives the knowledge of good and evil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}A river flowed out of Eden and watered the garden, and from there branched into four.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The name of the first is Pishon, which flows round the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The gold of that land is pure and there is aromatic gum and the onyx stone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The name of the second river is Gihon, which flows around the whole land of Cush,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and the name of the third river is the Tigris, which heads toward the east of Asshur. The fourth river is the Euphrates.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then the {\scaps Lord} God took the human and placed him in the garden of Eden to till it and to care for it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The {\scaps Lord} God also gave the human this command: \uc1\u8220*You may freely eat from every tree of the garden,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}except from the tree that gives the knowledge of good and evil; from this you must not eat, for on the day that you eat from it you will surely die.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Then the {\scaps Lord} God said, \uc1\u8220*It is not good for the human to be alone; I will make a helper suited to him.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}So out of the ground the {\scaps Lord} God formed all the wild beasts and birds, and made them come to the human to see what he would call them. Whatever he called each living creature, that was its name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}So the human, Adam gave names to all cattle and all the wild birds and beasts. But there was no companion suitable for him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Then the {\scaps Lord} God caused the human to fall into a deep sleep, and while he slept, he took one of his ribs and closed up its place with flesh.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}With the rib which he had taken from the human, the {\scaps Lord} built up a woman and brought her to the human.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then the human said, \uc1\u8220*This now is bone of my bone and flesh of my flesh. She will be called Woman, for from man she was taken.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For this reason a man leaves his father and his mother and clings to his wife, and the two become one flesh.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}The man and his wife were both naked, yet felt no shame.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Now the snake was craftier than any other wild beast that the {\scaps Lord} God had made. It said to the woman, \uc1\u8220*Has God really said, \uc1\u8216*You must not eat from any tree of the garden\uc1\u8217*?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The woman answered, \uc1\u8220*We are allowed to eat the fruit of all the trees of the garden;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}it is only about the fruit of the tree in the middle of the garden that God has said, \uc1\u8216*You must not eat from it, nor should you touch it, for if you do, you will die.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then the snake said to the woman, \uc1\u8220*You will not die!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}God knows that on the day you eat some of it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like gods, knowing what is good and what is evil.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When the woman saw that the tree was good for food, attractive to look at and desirable for acquiring wisdom, she took some of its fruit and ate. Then she gave some to her husband who was with her, and he ate.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they realized that they were naked, so they sewed fig-leaves together to cover themselves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But when they heard the sound of the {\scaps Lord} God walking in the garden in the evening breeze, the man and his wife hid from him among the garden trees.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}When the {\scaps Lord} God called to the man, \uc1\u8220*Where are you?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}he replied, \uc1\u8220*I heard you in the garden and I was afraid, because I was naked, so I hid myself.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The {\scaps Lord} God said, \uc1\u8220*Who told you that you were naked? Did you eat from the tree from which I ordered you not to eat?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The man answered, \uc1\u8220*The woman you placed beside me, she gave me fruit from the tree and I ate.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The {\scaps Lord} God said to the woman, \uc1\u8220*What is this that you have done?\uc1\u8221* The woman replied, \uc1\u8220*The snake deceived me, and I ate.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then the {\scaps Lord} God said to the snake:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Because you have done this,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you will be more accursed than all cattle
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and all the wild beasts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You will crawl on your belly
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and eat dust
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all your life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will establish hostility between you and the woman,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
between your offspring and hers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who will wound your head,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and you will wound their heel.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}To the woman he said,
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will greatly increase your anguished toil in pregnancy;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
with pain will you bear children.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You will yearn for your husband,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but he will rule over you.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}To Adam he said,
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Because you have listened to the voice of your wife,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and ate from the tree
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
about which I ordered you:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8217*You must never eat from it\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the ground will be cursed because of you;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as long as you live, you will earn a living only by anguished toil.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The ground will always bring forth thorns and thistles,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and you will eat the plants of the field.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}By the sweat of your brow you will eat bread,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
until you return to the ground,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for from it you were taken;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for dust you are,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and to dust you will return!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}The man, Adam, named his wife Eve{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn  Heb Havvah, that is, Life. }; because she was the mother of all living people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}The {\scaps Lord} God made clothes from animal skins for Adam and his wife and dressed them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Then the {\scaps Lord} God said: \uc1\u8220*The man has become like one of us, knowing good and evil. He must not reach out his hand, and take also from the tree of life, and eat, and live forever.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}So the {\scaps Lord} God sent him out of the garden of Eden, to till the ground from which he had been taken.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}He drove out Adam and he placed at the east of the garden of Eden the cherubim, and the blazing whirling sword, to bar the way to the tree of life.        
\par}

