{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The messenger of the {\scaps Lord} found her by a spring of water in the wilderness, by the spring in the way to Shur.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He said, \uc1\u8220*Hagar, Sarai\uc1\u8217*s slave-girl, where have you come from? And where are you going?\uc1\u8221* She said, \uc1\u8220*I am fleeing from the presence of mistress Sarai.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said to her, \uc1\u8220*Return to your mistress and submit yourself to her authority.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Moreover the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said to her, \uc1\u8220*I will make your descendants so many that they can not be numbered because they are so numerous.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The messenger of the {\scaps Lord} also said to her, \uc1\u8220*You are pregnant, and will have a son; you must call him Ishmael God hears, because the {\scaps Lord} has heard of your ill-treatment.\uc1\u8221*
