{\cf1\f1\fs22 17}When Abram was ninety-nine years old, the {\scaps Lord} revealed himself to Abram and said to him, \uc1\u8220*I am God Almighty, walk before me and be blameless{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and I will make my solemn agreement between me and you and will make your descendants exceedingly numerous.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then Abram fell on his face; and God talked with him, saying{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*I make this solemn promise to you: you will be the father of a multitude of nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Neither will your name any longer be Abram, but your name will be Abraham; for I will make you the father of a multitude of nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and will make nations of you, and kings shall spring from you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}I will establish my solemn agreement between me and you and your descendants after your throughout their generations, an everlasting covenant, to be a God to you and to your descendants after you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I will give to you, and to your descendants after your, the land where you are now foreigners, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession, and I will be their God.\uc1\u8221*
